properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 27 at 3:01PM PST until January 28 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow with 8 to 12 inches of accumulation expected at
Hurricane Ridge tonight and Tuesday morning.

* WHERE...Olympic mountains including Hurricane Ridge,

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Expect winter driving conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The snow level will rise to around 5000
feet later this evening and then fall to around 3500 feet
Tuesday. Dangerous avalanche conditions are expected to develop
across the Cascades this evening and very dangerous conditions
may develop tonight into Tuesday. Expect the threat of large and
potentially naturally-triggered avalanches.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST TUESDAY
